==English==

===Verb===
'''chode'''
# {{archaic}} Past tense of to [[chide]]

===Quotations===
*'''1611:''' And Jacob was wroth, and '''chode''' with Laban: and Jacob answered and said to Laban, What is my trespass? what is my sin, that thou hast so hotly pursued after me? &mdash; [[w:King James Bible|King James Bible]], Genesis 31:36
*'''1611:''' And the people '''chode''' with Moses, and spake, saying, Would God that we had died when our brethren died before the LORD! &mdash; [[w:King James Bible|King James Bible]], Numbers 20:30

===Usage notes===
*The above quotations show this form of the verb intransitively followed by "with"; it is unclear whether it can also be used transitively.
